<br>
He starts sending me tells, asking me where I am, and when he finds me he inspects me about twenty times.  Then the usual lovely dialogue ensues.  He says he really needs my equipment for his new character.  He offers me 5k for my runed falchion (?!?), claiming that he'll pay me back with his level 55 necromancer, &quot;Zakk.&quot;<br>
<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:00:58 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'it is on Zakk my 55 necro'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:01:05 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'very respected '<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:01:11 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'you know him??'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:01:27 2001] You told Ozbillious, 'No, I don't.'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:01:40 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'what lvl are u?'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:01:42 2001] You told Ozbillious, 'If you bring the Necro here, I'll gladly trade with you.'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:02:41 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'I would really apriciate it if you could put it on this guy here'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:03:01 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'My 55 necro Zakk is very honorable'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:03:04 2001] You told Ozbillious, 'Sorry, I do a fair trade... money for item at the same time.'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:03:31 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'that wouldnt work because i need the sword on this guy'<br>
[Sat Jan 20 04:03:42 2001] Ozbillious tells you, 'I am trustworthy'<br>
<br>
/em rolls on the floor laughing at the lame scammer.<br>
<br>
I refrained from telling the guy where to go, figuring that public humiliation would be so much more fun.  He walked away empty-handed, and immediately camped out.  I do an /ooc and let the zone know what just went on, and get several tells from people who had been approached by him under different names.<br>
<br>
I ported over to WC, and not ten minutes later I run into a level 1 monk named Soltonya (er something) who was trying to talk an Ogre warrior out of his Lamentations.  This was in the North FP bank.  I sent the Ogre a tell and told him what the newbie had been up to all night, and we had a good laugh embarassing the little bastage.<br>
<br>
Do people actually get scammed this way?  Does this actually WORK?  Anyway, if you are approached by some little level 1 who wants your gear, laugh in his face and tell him Verdana sends her regards...<br>
