<br>
Look at the fungal tunic that ends up in everyones trade window in EC. All I have to do is go into EC and auction something of value for someone to offer me something. Do people fall for the the 5ks on my other character? Yes.<br>
<br>
So yes its bound to work. Why? Let me explain. I trade items. I buy cheaply because I pay atttention to prices and I sell that item for more than I paid. Now some guy will tell me &quot;but its only worth 500pp&quot; I know what he means is that its only worth 500pp to him. If I hild on long enough someone will come into the zone looking to buy something and Ill be there. I'll sell my item for a nice profit. If your prepared to hang on you can make a fortune. People do this every day in real life. <br>
<br>
So you put that fungi tunic in a window 100 times and at least 1 person is going to fall for it. You may have to try the &quot;but its on my other character&quot; trick 200 times and someone is going to fall for it once. Maybe its a younger player, maybe its someone who is too trusting. Maybe its someone who thinks that theyve heard the well respected name before.<br>
<br>
So as for being creative. Why? Baiting and switching is far more creative than asking if someone will trust you and give you the item and you'll pay them later but it has entirely more risk. If you bait and switch you havent got long before someone petitions you. If you offer money from a higher level character you can always get away on the basis that you may intend to pay for it. All you have to do is make sure that you can pay for it if anything goes wrong and the GMs get involved.<br>
<br>
Heres a better one. Start a character called Verdaana or Keryn. People know the names, theyve seen us on the boards, they know we can pay for an item like this. So if someone goes up to someone and calls themselves by a similar sounding name then they can pretend to be our twinks.<br>
<br>
Eventually it will work. It only has to work once and that newbie has enough cash to outfit themselves completely. Only 1 dragonborne sash has to be given for that cloth shirt and some mid level guy (cos thats usually who they are) has a decent item.<br>
<br>
So now some people are thinking Kerryns a scammer cos he knows all the tricks. Know the nature of the beast before you attempt to kill it.<br>
<br>
The biggest protection you can offer yourselves like this is to only trade for an item in trade. Even with people yove known forever. So Zakk can give Verdaana the money and then have a friend swap it for him.<br>
<br>
Whats the next step. Let everyone know who your twinks are. If anyone comes up to you and says Im Kerryn can you lend me this and Ill pay you back later know this. I have two twinks. Rylan (level 5 druid)and Nottin (level 1 necro). If Keryn asks you for an item. ITS NOT ME!!!!<br>
<br>
You can petition it all you like but were past the days when this worked on a single account. People buy accounts for this purpose. You get one account banned and they'll buy another. You can have their IP address banned but people will use alternative dial ups. They can ban peoples home addresses but they'll ask a relative to use their address. You can ban a credit card but who couldnt ask a friend if they could borrow theirs.<br>
<br>
Their is no protection in the long run. So Verant can trace that item but what happens if Ozbillious trades that Runed Falchion for 800pp and gives the 800pp to the twink. You cant trace the falchioon any where else but to someone who bought it legitamately.<br>
<br>
The only thing you can do is cover yourself any way you can.<br>
<br>
